    "stac_version": "1.1.0",
    "description": "The CLOUD_GPC suite provides cloud properties derived from the GISS Polarimetric Cloud (GPC) algorithm, along with additional variables obtained through combination with the OCI CLOUD suite.\n\nGiven the novelty of implementing a polarimetric algorithm on a global scale, note that several experimental variables\u2014particularly those intended for diagnostic purposes and future refinement\u2014are included and may change in subsequent, more mature versions.\nCore geophysical variables in this suite include:\n \u2022 cloud_droplet_effective_radius / variance - Cloud droplet effective radius and variance (\u00b5m, unitless)\n \u2022 cloud_droplet_number_concentration - Droplet number concentration (combining with OCI CLOUD) (cm\u207b\u00b3)\n \u2022 cloud_liquid_water_path - Cloud liquid water path (combining with OCI CLOUD) (g m\u207b\u00b2)\n \u2022 cloud_liquid_index - Index measuring polarized primary bow strength (unitless)\n \u2022 cloud_optical_thickness - Cloud optical thickness (from OCI CLOUD) (unitless)\n \u2022 cloud_bow_extinction_cross_section_Xnm \u2013 355/532 nm extinction cross section based on Cloud Bow retrievals\n \u2022 cloud_bow_lidar_ratio_Xnm \u2013 355/532 lidar ratios based on Cloud Bow retrievals\n \u2022 cloud_rft_* - Retrievals from Rainbow Fourier Transform (experimental and exploratory, intended for future substantial refinements)\n \u2022 cloud_top_properties - Cloud top altitude (m), pressure (hPa), and temperature (K) (from OCI CLOUD)\n",
